column8: Major viral transcription factor ICP4 homolog

column12: The ORF sequence was used to order synthetic peptide derived from VZV strain vOka.  Truncation analyses were not done to identify minimal epitope or epitopes.  Minimal epitope may be shorter than the listed peptide.  It is possible more than one clonotype of T-cells is present in the polyclonal CD4 T-cell line population that can respond to the listed peptide, such that more than one minimal epitope is contained within the listed peptide sequence.  Similarly, reactivity was detected with the same synthetic peptide in some cases amongst VZV-reactive CD4 T-cell lines from multiple donors. Since we do not know if the same minimal peptide is being recognized or if the same HLA restriction element is used in different donors, we have provided more than one epitope record in these situations.
